<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION WITH TRAILING LEAF SPRINGS - MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER (Figure 11 ,Figure 12 andFigure
        13 ) - REMOVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block front wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise vehicle and support axle with stands.</para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>A jack must never be used alone to support a vehicle while under chassis service is being
                        performed. The jack may lower and serious personal injury could result. Always support vehicle
                        with floor stands.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dump air pressure from air springs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rebound bolt, lock nut, washers, spacer tube and rebound roller from frame hanger.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise rear of frame high enough to remove load from main support member.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove U-bolts locknuts and washers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove U-bolts, bottom cap, and top pad.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both locknuts and washers which connect the air spring mounting brackets to both main
                support members.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift air spring mounting brackets off the main support members with jacks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove main support member assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
